<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Affine 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus farinosi" order="Solanales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="farinosi">Convolvulus farinosi</taxonomicName>
L. et 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Abh. Koenigl. Akad. Wiss. Berlin 2: 349. 1892. (Engler" authorityYear="1892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus aschersonii" order="Solanales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aschersonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Convolvulus aschersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Engler sed pilis asperis, longis instructis et lobis medianis foliorum inciso-dentatis distinctis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Abh. Koenigl. Akad. Wiss. Berlin 2: 349. 1892. (Engler" authorityYear="1892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus aschersonii" order="Solanales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aschersonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Convolvulus aschersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse (1958</bibRefCitation>
: 677).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
ZIMBABWE, Salisbury [Harare], a weed, 29 June 1927, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">R.G. Young 18497</emphasis>
(holotype BM001035803!; isotype PRE).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
Perennial herb, all vegetative parts pubescent with somewhat asperous, sometimes rufous hairs; rootstock a woody taproot; stems prostrate or twining, up to 2 m long. Leaves petiolate, 3-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-2.5 cm, variable in shape, ovate-deltoid, auriculate, sometimes the auricles lobed, the central lobe commonly oblong, apex acute, the margins undulate, sinuate-dentate to pinnatisect, base hastate; petioles 3-30 mm. Flowers 1-6 together (very rarely all solitary on the same plant) in axillary pedunculate cymes; peduncles 10-35 mm; pedicels 2-15 mm, bracts 2.5-4 mm, linear; sepals very unequal, outer sepals 6-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 mm, ovate to elliptic, acute; inner sepals 4-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, nearly glabrous, apiculate; corolla 9-12 mm long, white or pale pink, lobed, the midpetaline bands pubescent, terminating in prominent teeth; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 3 mm above base, stigmas 2.5 mm, linear. Capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous, smooth. [
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Southern Africa" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 138" refId="B226" refString="Meeuse, ADL, Welman, WG, 2000. Convolvulaceae. Flora of Southern Africa volume 28 (part 1): 1 - 138" title="Convolvulaceae." volume="volume 28" year="2000">Meeuse and Welman 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 38 (map), under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Abh. Koenigl. Akad. Wiss. Berlin 2: 349. 1892. (Engler" authorityYear="1892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus aschersonii" order="Solanales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aschersonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Convolvulus aschersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
South Africa (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<pageBreakToken pageId="75" pageNumber="76" start="start">Codd</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
8732, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Meeuse</emphasis>
2237, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Hutchinson</emphasis>
2895, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Codd</emphasis>
8732); Zimbabwe (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Blenkison in Moss</emphasis>
14811, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Peter</emphasis>
51118, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Drummond</emphasis>
4904, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Leach</emphasis>
8369); Zambia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Fanshawe</emphasis>
6566); Ethiopia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Mooney</emphasis>
5548). It is centred on Northern South Africa-Zimbabwe and is absent north of southern Zambia apart from two collections from Ethiopia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
This species was treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Abh. Koenigl. Akad. Wiss. Berlin 2: 349. 1892. (Engler" authorityYear="1892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus aschersonii" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aschersonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus aschersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse (1958)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Southern Africa" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 138" refId="B226" refString="Meeuse, ADL, Welman, WG, 2000. Convolvulaceae. Flora of Southern Africa volume 28 (part 1): 1 - 138" title="Convolvulaceae." volume="volume 28" year="2000">Meeuse and Welman (2000)</bibRefCitation>
but is very different from the type of that species. It is distinguished from all similar species by the spreading pubescent, slightly asperous indumentum of stem, leaves and flower parts, the pinnatisect leaves and (usually) the 4-6-flowered cymes. Towards the north of its range it tends to have fewer flowers and specimens intermediate with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker, Bull Misc. Inform. Kew 1894: 67. 1894. (Baker" authorityYear="1894" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus thomsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thomsonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus thomsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Abh. Koenigl. Akad. Wiss. Berlin 2: 349. 1892. (Engler" authorityYear="1892" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus aschersonii" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aschersonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus aschersonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are sometimes found. Although quite often united with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, BRM" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1287 - 1306" publicationUrl="10.12705/636.9" refId="B388" refString="Williams, BRM, Mitchell, TC, Wood, JRI, Harris, DJ, Scotland, RW, Carine, MA, 2014. Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L. Taxon 63: 1287 - 1306, DOI: 10.12705/636.9" title="Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L." url="10.12705/636.9" volume="63" year="2014">Williams et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) support of the retention of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus austroafricanus" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus austroafricanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus austroafricanus" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus austroafricanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common in the area where Zimbabwe and South Africa meet and should be classified as Least Concen (LC) using 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="International Union for the Conservation of Nature, Gland, Switzerland" pageId="204" pageNumber="205" refId="B159" refString="IUCN, 2012. Guidelines for application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional and National Levels. International Union for the Conservation of Nature, Gland, Switzerland" title="Guidelines for application of IUCN Red List Criteria at Regional and National Levels" year="2012">IUCN (2012)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines. The epithet &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">austroafricanus</emphasis>
&quot; meaning southern Africa refers to its distribution.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
A cultivated plant (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Meeuse</emphasis>
9237A) looks very like a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus austroafricanus" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="austroafricanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus austroafricanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L., Mant. Pl. 2: 203. 1771 (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus farinosus" order="Solanales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="farinosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Convolvulus farinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
